ack.title: Acknowledgements
ack.p: This research did not receive any specific grant from funding agencies in the public, commercial, or not-for-profit sectors. Conflicts of interests: none declared. We thank the Dutch Working Group for Clinical Virology (NWKV) for the use of virology diagnostic reports (non-sentinel data) and Erny Wentink (research assistant), the GPs and their patients of the national sentinel surveillance network (NIVEL Primary Care Database) for taking swabs and providing epidemiological and demographic information. The team of technicians at RIVM currently represented by Pieter Overduin, Sharon van den Brink, Lisa Wijsman, Ton Marzec and Gabriel Goderski are thanked for organizing the logistics and performing testing of the sentinel specimens. We thank Paul Bijkerk from the Dutch National Institute for Public Health and the Environment (RIVM) and GÃ© Donker, coordinator sentinel practices, Nivel Primary Care Database, for their permission to replicate figures on geographic distribution of non-sentinel laboratories and sentinel practices ( Supplementary Figure S1).
